10.1016/j.asoc.2021.107230 Deyu Zhou, Dayou Zhong, Yulan He, et al. 2014. Biomedical relation extraction: from binary to complex. Computational and mathematical methods in medicine 2014 (2014). Huiwei Zhou, Yibin Xu, Weihong Yao, Zhe Liu, Chengkun Lang, and Haibin Jiang. 2020b. Global Context-enhanced Graph Convolutional Networks for Document-level Relation Extraction. In Proceedings of the 28th International Conference on Computational Linguistics . International Committee on Computational Linguistics, Barcelona, Spain (Online), 5259–5270. https://doi.org/10.18653/v1/2020.coling- main.461 Wenxuan Zhou, Kevin Huang, Tengyu Ma, and Jing Huang. 2020a. Document-Level Relation Extraction with Adaptive Thresholding and Localized Context Pooling. arXiv:2010.11304 [cs.CL] , Vol. 1, No. 1, Article . Publication date: October 2023.A Comprehensive Survey of Document-level Relation Extraction (2016-2023) • 35 A COMPARATIVE RESULTS ON DWIE Model IgnF1 F1 CNN ♠ 34.65 46.14 LSTM ♠ 40.81 52.60 BLSTM ♠ 42.03 54.47 Context-Aware ♠ 45.37 56.58 CorefBERT ♣ 61.71 66.59 GAIN ♠ 62.37 67.57 SSAN ♣ 62.58 69.39 ATLOP ♠ 62.09 69.94 CorefBERT+RSMAN [Yu et al. 2022] 62.01 67.52 SSAN+RSMAN [Yu et al. 2022] 63.42 70.95 BERT𝑏𝑎𝑠𝑒 (2022) [Han et al. 2022] 62.92 69.12 BERT+Correlation [Han et al. 2022] 65.64 71.56 Table 7. Comparative Results on the DWIE dataset [Zaporojets et al. 2021]. Results with ♠and ♣come from Ru et al. [2021] and Yu et al. [2022], respectively. , Vol. 1, No. 1, Article . Publication date: October 2023.",
